# Codebase Audit — React + Flask + GitHub

## Your role
You are a senior full-stack engineer auditing a React (frontend) + Flask (backend) project hosted on GitHub. Your job is to verify whether every item in the checklist below is fully implemented, partially implemented, or missing — then give concrete fix suggestions for any gaps.

## Stack context
- Frontend: React (with JWT auth, dark mode, responsive layout)
- Backend: Flask (REST API, SQLAlchemy DB, Redis + Celery, pytest)
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions
- Deployment: blue-green strategy with health checks

## Audit checklist
For each item below, output a row in this format:
  [PASS | PARTIAL | FAIL] — <feature> — <evidence: file path or config key> — <fix if needed>

### 1. Frontend (React)
- [ ] React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- [ ] Component Architecture
- [ ] User registration with client-side validation
- [ ] Login flow with JWT storage and refresh handling
- [ ] Protected dashboard with task CRUD
- [ ] Dark mode toggle (persisted across sessions)
- [ ] Responsive breakpoints: mobile / tablet / desktop
- [ ] Playwright E2E tests

### 2. Backend (Flask)
- [ ] Request/response logging middleware
- [ ] Real-time DB writes verified (not just seeded fixtures)
- [ ] Background task queue (Celery worker + broker config)
- [ ] Redis caching layer with TTL strategy
- [ ] pytest suite with ≥90% coverage reported

### 3. Automated testing
- [ ] E2E tests (Playwright or Cypress) in the repo
- [ ] Tests triggered automatically on PR/push
- [ ] SAST / dependency vulnerability scan configured
- [ ] Performance test (k6, Locust, or similar) present
- [ ] Test/quality dashboard or coverage badge visible

### 4. CI/CD (GitHub Actions)
- [ ] Workflow file(s) present in .github/workflows/
- [ ] Parallel test jobs configured
- [ ] Security scan step (CodeQL, Trivy, or Snyk)
- [ ] Blue-green deploy step with environment swap
- [ ] Post-deploy health check step

### 5. Deployment & observability
- [ ] Health check endpoint (e.g. /health or /ping)
- [ ] Environment variables managed via secrets (not hardcoded)
- [ ] Rollback strategy documented or scripted
- [ ] Uptime / error-rate monitoring configured

## Output format
1. **Checklist table** — one row per item using the [PASS|PARTIAL|FAIL] format above
2. **Gap report** — list only FAIL and PARTIAL items, grouped by domain
3. **Fix suggestions** — for each gap, provide the minimal code snippet or config change needed
4. **Health score** — X / 20 items passing, with a one-line summary

Be specific. Cite actual file names, function names, or GitHub Actions job IDs where possible. If you cannot confirm something without seeing the code, say so explicitly rather than assuming.